**How to fix execution failures:**
- "expected: <X> but was: <Y>" → Your assertion expected the wrong value. Verify the actual
  behavior of the focal method and correct the expected value.
- "NullPointerException" → Add null checks or ensure objects are properly initialized before use.
- "NoSuchMethodException" / "NoSuchFieldException" → The private method/field name is wrong.
  Use the correct field/method name as it appears in the source code.
- IOException not thrown → The mock/setup is not correctly triggering the exception path.
  Review the test setup and use a properly configured mock or failing Reader.

