## BUG_REVEALING ISSUES (tests run but do not reveal the bug)
Transform tests into bug-seeking ones:
- Break assumptions: null, empty, invalid, extreme inputs
- Force rare paths: error conditions, edge branches
- Stateful testing: multiple calls, reuse objects, check state consistency
- Exception testing: trigger and assert exceptions
- Strengthen assertions: exact values, invariants, expected failures
- Do not only tweak assertions — change inputs and test structure.
{% if contract_text %}
- Use the Program Contract above to identify what the method GUARANTEES — then assert those guarantees hold.
- For each precondition violation, use assertThrows to verify proper error handling.
